  m_Name: Radius_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Radius_L
  partName: Radius Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left radius is a long forearm bone located on the medial side of the canine
    left forelimb and functions as a major weight-bearing structure. It forms joints
    with the humerus at the elbow and with the carpal bones at the wrist, supporting
    smooth and coordinated limb movement.
  - Numerous muscles and ligaments attach to the radius, enabling controlled motion
    of the paw and carpal region during locomotion. The bone contributes to shock
    absorption, stability, and force transmission while walking, running, and jumping.
